    "ocr_text": "645

Oct. 15, 1909

DF
Mr. Ed. Stephenson, Organizer,
American Federation of Labor,
211 Rupert St., Winnipeg, Canada.
Dear Sir and Brother:

Your favor of the 11th instant is received and I thank
you for your kind expressions in regard to my return home after
the European trip. I am indeed glad to get back, but as you can
very readily imagine, there is an enormous amount of work before
me previous to the convention, which meets in Toronto, on November
8th.

I note what you say in regard to the workingmen's
Compensation Bill and your request to be put in touch with the
Labor Legislation Association. I presume you refer to the
American Association for Labor Legislation. If you will write to
Prof. John R. Commons, University of Wisconsin, Madison, Wisconsin,
who is secretary of this Association, I am sure he will be glad to give you any information within his power.

With kind regards and hoping to hear from you whenever
convenient, I am,

Fraternally yours,

(President)
American Federation of Labor.",
